            "id": "4577988",
            "title": "Evercore Q1 dividend preview: 18-year streak set for another raise",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Evercore (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/EVR\" title=\"Evercore Inc.\">EVR</a></span></span>) is expected to announce a dividend increase this April, continuing its 18-year streak of regular dividend growth.</p>\n<p>Based on past trends, analysts expect a consensus annual dividend of about ~$3.50 per share. This equals a quarterly dividend of ~0.875 per share, which implies an increase of ~4.16% from the current ~$0.840 per share payout.</p>\n<p>The company last paid a dividend of ~$0.840 per share in January 2026, which comes to an annual yield of 0.95%.(needs to be confirmed)</p>\n<p>Earlier, in April last year, it increased the dividend by ~5%, to ~$0.840 from ~$0.800. </p>\n<p>Over the past five years, Evercore has delivered a dividend growth rate of ~2.45% and currently maintains a payout ratio of ~23.14%</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, on dividend quality metrics, the company carries ratings of A+ for safety, A+ for growth, F for yield, and A- for consistency.</p>\n<p>Evercore is set to release its Q1 2026 financial results on April 29, 2026, before the opening bell.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
